			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just want to share with you what we have installed to fight spam. It works well, there are no spam posts although we have guest posting active on all forum sections.
<br />

<br />
We use the following MODs:
<br />

<br />
1. Anti Bot Question MOD. This mod replaces the default phpBB visual confirmation captcha system with various question types (math additions, etc). Adds it to registrations and to guest post submission. Allows for full configuration of captcha and supports multiple fonts. Uses pull down multiple choice to make entering answers easier. We noticed that when using individual questions bots can submit posts so we disabled them and only have automatic generated verifications. Since then no more troubles.
<br />

<br />
2. Links Rejector
<br />

<br />
3. Extended Censoring Mod. This mod just extends the words in Word Censor list to all areas of your forum.
<br />

<br />
With the three above we have no more spams. We also installed following (optional) mods.
<br />

<br />
1. No Website Signature during registration. This removes the website link and signature box on registration page. Option to auto ban IPs who try this.
<br />

<br />
2. Remove Sid For Guests (Search Engine Optimization). This mod allows you to remove SID for guests, for bots or for all. It has ACP configuration and works really well.
<br />

<br />
If you have any questions let me know, happy to help fight spam!
<br />

<br />
DickS</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
