			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi,
<br />

<br />
Well, ABQ generates images instead of text questions and offers a multiple choice option which makes answering the questions easier.
<br />

<br />
ABQ also has an &quot;individual&quot; question option that is similar to TC. But I noticed that bots can get past that since its text based. Since we changed to full automatic questions the guest post attempts have been a few daily.
<br />

<br />
Take a look how it works: <a href="http://www.pamela-systems.com/forum" target="_blank">www.pamela-systems.com/forum</a>
<br />

<br />
In addition we replaced the &quot;No Website Signature&quot; Mod with the &quot;Only Active Members can post URLs&quot; Mod which means that only after making x posts a member can complete the profile and post links. This as we do not require user confirmation at registration.
<br />

<br />
We will monitor how this goes, the most difficult thing is keeping the board simple enough to use and still keeping out spam.
<br />

<br />
Definitely LinksRejector is one of the best mods out there and helped up many many times. This is a MUST HAVE mod no matter what other mods you have.
<br />

<br />
DickS</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
